<br>
Dear Members,<br>
<br>
The Internet Society is now accepting applications for its Community Grants Programme.<br>
<br>
The application cycle will be open until midnight PST on 1 October 2013, (aka 0700 UTC on 2 October).<br>
<br>
Grant notifications will be made at the end of November 2013.<br>
<br>
ABOUT THE PROGRAMME<br>
<br>
To learn more about the programme please visit our website at:<br>
<br>
[English] <a href="http://www.internetsociety.org/communitygrants" target="_blank">http://www.internetsociety.org/communitygrants</a><br>
[French] <a href="http://www.internetsociety.org/fr/subventions%C3%A0lacommunaut%C3%A9" target="_blank">www.internetsociety.org/fr/subventionsàlacommunauté</a><br>
[Spanish] <a href="http://www.internetsociety.org/es/subvencionesalacomunidad" target="_blank">www.internetsociety.org/es/subvencionesalacomunidad</a><br>
<br>
**Good to know**<br>
<br>
•       The number of applications is limited to 2 per Member or Chapter.<br>
<br>
•       At least one letter of support must be uploaded to your application.<br>
<br>
•       Any support for your project that is more than US$500 should be validated with a support letter.<br>
<br>
Support Letters establish your project partners’ willingness to support your initiative and their engagement toward fulfilling your project’s goals. This demonstrates increased sustainability.<br>
<br>
<br>
HOW TO APPLY<br>
<br>
Please click on the &quot;Apply via ZoomGrants button&quot; on the applications page:<br>
<a href="http://www.internetsociety.org/what-we-do/grants-awards/community-grants/application-process" target="_blank">http://www.internetsociety.org/what-we-do/grants-awards/community-grants/application-process</a><br>
<br>
If you are new to the Programme, we recommend that you to view the ZoomGrants applicant tutorial before starting your application: <a href="http://www.zoomgrants.com/welcome/applicantslideshow.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.zoomgrants.com/welcome/applicantslideshow.pdf</a><br>


<br>
Any questions may be sent to <a href="mailto:projects@...">projects@...</a>.<br>
<br>
